/**
@mainpage HERMES Modem — ARQ Subsystem

@section intro Introduction

Mercury is the modem component of the
[HERMES project](https://www.rhizomatica.org/hermes/).
This documentation covers the ARQ data link subsystem API.

@section docs Documentation

- [ARQ Protocol & Architecture (ARQ.md)](https://github.com/Rhizomatica/mercury/blob/mercuryv2/docs/ARQ.md) —
  Full protocol reference, state machine, OTA tuning guide.
- [Mercury README](https://github.com/Rhizomatica/mercury/tree/mercuryv2) —
  Build instructions, CLI usage, logging.
- [mercury-qt GUI](https://github.com/Rhizomatica/mercury-qt) —
  Qt-based graphical interface (under development).

@section modules Key Modules

- @ref arq_protocol.h — Frame builders/parsers, wire format constants.
- @ref arq_fsm.h — Connection and data-flow state machines, gear-shifting.
- @ref arq.h — Event loop, channel bus, TCP bridge.
- @ref arq_timing.h — OTA timing instrumentation and logging.

@section links Links

- Source: https://github.com/Rhizomatica/mercury
- Mailing list: https://lists.riseup.net/www/info/hermes-general
- Funded by [ARDC](https://www.ardc.net/) and others.
*/
